                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2397</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-11T23:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1916, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Japanese are using agents to create panic Tsinanfu and to urge governor general
                    to declare independence. Railway station headquarters of armed brigands with
                    whom Chinese cannot interfere because station policed Japanese troops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
